Through these recordings, the Idaho Humanities Council provides a lasting resource that explores the human experience, fostering curiosity, dialogue, and deeper understanding of the world around us.

title: Historical Japanese Ceramic Comparative Collection (HJCCC)

description: The Historical Japanese Ceramic Comparative Collection (HJCCC) provides researchers with comparative examples of Japanese ceramics that are found on North American archaeological sites. The HJCCC contains digital photographs and resources for identifying and describing Japanese ceramics manufactured during the Meiji, Taisho, and early Showa eras (roughly the mid-nineteenth and early twentieth centuries). It is intended to assist in identification of historical Japanese ceramics, to encourage the use of standardized terminology, and to promote further research.

title: Joe Williams Collection
tagline: The International Jazz Collections
description: Joe Williams was a vocalist who began singing professionally in the late 1930's. He worked with the big bands of Coleman Hawkins, Lionel Hampton and Count Basie; it was with Basie that Williams had his first recording hits. Williams won many awards and professional recognition. In the 1980's he had a recurring role (as 'Grandpa Al') on TV's The Cosby Show. He died in Las Vegas on March 29, 1999.

description: Construction of the Kibbie Dome (now the P1FCU Kibbie Dome, previously the Kibbie-ASUI Activity Center), the University of Idaho's multipurpose athletic stadium, was completed in the summer of 1975. title: Vandal Video Collection
tagline: Historic videos of University of Idaho Basketball and Football Games, 1925 - 1997
description: The Vandal Video Collection is a collection of 160+ digitized 16mm Film reels that were scouting videos for both football and basketball games..

title: VERSO
tagline: Vandal Expertise, Research, and Scholarship Online
description: VERSO preserves and provides access to the research and creative output of the University of Idaho's faculty, students and staff. Fed from institutional and publicly accessible data, VERSO includes a network of web profiles and an archive of publications.
image_alt_text: Image of a person looking into a microscope in front of a computer.

title: Voices of Gay Rodeo
tagline: Oral Histories from the International Gay Rodeo Association
description: Partnering with the International Gay Rodeo Association to collect and preserve people's experiences as LGBTQ+ westerners, this project seeks to protect endangered histories and relocate LGBTQ+ people back into the American West as people continue to build resilient communities.
image_alt_text: man rides a horse in the rodeo ground with rainbow flag

description: A scrapbook of photos, correspondence, and clippings documenting WWAMI's early years from 1971 to 1975.

title: Web Archive Collections
tagline: Preserving Access to Unique Born Digital Content
description: To ensure continued access to the unique born-digital content published on University of Idaho websites, the Library proactively captures university communications in their original web context. These materials are made available in our digital collections and as part of larger web archives.
